<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881003-0049 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business: Penn Traffic Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> PNF </CO><IN> BON STK </IN><TEXT>   PENN TRAFFIC Co. said it offered 185,000 units of Pandamp;C Food Markets Inc., through Salomon Brothers Inc. Each unit, priced at $1,140, consists of $1,000 principal amount of 13 3/4% senior subordinated notes due 1998 and five shares of 8% convertible preferred stock at $28 a share. After the initial sale, the notes and preferred stock may be traded separately. Proceeds will be used principally to repay debt incurred in the acquisition of Pandamp;C's parent, Pandamp;C Foods Inc. by Penn Traffic earlier this year. Penn Traffic, a Johnstown, Pa., affiliate of Miller Tabak Hirsch andamp; Co., is a wholesale and retail food distributor. </TEXT></DOC>